-- PERF: the ~1.2s periodic stutter IS the library autosave — every 1.2s it re-serializes
-- the whole config and writefile()s it (a disk-write freeze). A SINGLE SetAutoSave(false)
-- does NOT stick: the lib runs an ASYNC autoload coroutine (task.spawn) that fires a tick
-- or two AFTER CreateWindow returns and RESTORES the persisted "autosave:" pref from disk
-- (`if ln~=nil then az.autoSave=ln end`), clobbering our disable back to true. So we
-- re-assert false for the first several seconds. The autoload only runs ONCE (it's guarded
-- by _didAutoload), so once we win the race after it fires, autosave stays off for good.
-- Verfall persists via the named config save in Settings instead. (We deliberately DON'T
-- enable lite/perf mode — it strips the menu animations that make it feel smooth.)
pcall(function() Lib:SetAutoSave(false) end)
task.spawn(function()
    -- SetAutoSave is pure-Lua (just sets az.autoSave, no bridge), so re-asserting it is free.
    -- Pin it OFF FOREVER at 1Hz: the library's async autoload can re-enable autosave from the
    -- persisted pref a tick or two — or longer — after CreateWindow, so a fixed 12s window can
    -- expire before the clobber lands and the 1.2s writefile stutter comes back. A permanent
    -- 1Hz re-assert defeats it for good (the autoload only fires once per session).
    while GUI.Running do
        task.wait(1)
        pcall(function() Lib:SetAutoSave(false) end)
    end
end)

